                         JIC - JIRA CLI Client

MOTIVATION
----------

To get a tool that is easy to use for us, keyboard junkies.

git CLI is used as a main source of ideas so JIC should not have a steep
learning curve for anyone who's already git-enabled. :)


SOURCES
-------

JIC sources are hosted at GitHub git server:

    https://github.com/ototo/jic

To clone the repo use:

    https://github.com/ototo/jic


VERSIONING
----------

Version number is date-based and is:

    YY.WK.REV

where

    YY -    is last two digits of the current year
    WK -    is the current week's number
    REV -   (optional) is a bugfixing increment


CONTRIBUTING
------------

Please join jic-dev mailing list hosted by Linaro:
http://lists.linaro.org/mailman/listinfo/jic-dev


